label: rubber cement
definition: A glue which is composed of elastic polymers mixed in a solvent.
comment: Solvents typically used include acetone, hexane, heptane or toluene.

label: wallpaper paste
definition: A glue which is 1) composed primarily of methyl cellulose and water, and 2) intended to fix wallpaper to walls.

label: permanent hair dye
definition: A chemical colorant which is 1) manufactured and 2) primarily composed of hydrogen peroxide and ammonia, and 3) when applied to hair, can alter the natural hair pigments for 6-8 weeks.

label: pharmaceutical ink
definition: A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured, 2) composed of alcohol, titanium dioxide, and propylene glycol, and 3) intended for use as an ingestible ink for medicine pills.

label: gel ink
definition: A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured, 2) composed of copper phthalocyanine, iron oxides, water, and biopolymers and 3) intended for use in pens.

label: soy ink
definition: A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured and 2) primarily composed of soybean oil, as well as pigment, resin, and wax.

label: aqueous inkjet printer ink
definition: A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured, 2) primarily composed of water, as well as glycol, and dye, and 3) intended for use in inkjet printers.

label: emissions from petroleum combustion
definition: A material entity which is composed primarily of gases and particles produced by the combustion of petroleum fuels.

label: colorant fluid
definition: A manufactured product which 1) contains at least one colorant substance capable of absorbing light in the visible range dissolved or suspended in a solvent and 2) can imprint colorant upon materials.

label: chemical colorant
definition: A manufactured product which contains at least one chemical substance that when applied to a material, causes a chemical reaction resulting in the alteration of the materialâ€™s light absorption in the visible range.
